# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Module Map

This profile maps the minimum durable lanes that every Sula-managed project should keep visible.

## Core Lanes

| Path | Responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `{{APP_SHELL_PATH}}` | primary project entry or overview anchor |
| `{{API_LAYER_PATH}}` | current execution or orchestration lane |
| `{{STATE_LAYER_PATH}}` | generated current-state snapshot |
| `.sula/sources/registry.json` | registered project source anchors |
| `.sula/events/log.jsonl` | append-only kernel event history |
| `{{STATUS_FILE}}` | human-readable current project state |
| `{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}}` | durable change-history index |

## Modification Rules

- keep stable project truth in project-owned files first
- use `.sula/` for kernel state, indexes, and generated views
- when a request changes durable operating behavior, update state and traceability together

## Coordination Rule

If a request changes both project truth and project memory, update:

1. source files or source documents
2. durable state and change records
3. exported recall views if they are part of the local workflow
